            <title>[SEC-1425] AbstractRememberMeServices not handling properly empty cookie</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1425</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Whwn empty cookie is sent to AbstractRememberMeServices, it will throw java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException instead of org.springframework.security.web.authentication.rememberme.InvalidCookieException&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be fixed by adding &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (tokens.length == 0) {&lt;br/&gt;
    throw new InvalidCookieException( &quot;No cookie!?&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;after &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;String[] tokens = StringUtils.delimitedListToStringArray(cookieAsPlainText, DELIMITER);&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
